{
  "texts": [
    "Across experiments, DRaFT-Q exhibits dynamic rank behavior, stable convergence, and up to 4-6% accuracy improvements over static-rank PEFT baselines.",
    "Notably, these gains are achieved with no additional model parameters and within the same VRAM budget.In summary, DRaFT-Q offers a practical, lightweight extension to existing PEFT frameworks.",
    "By combining dynamic structural adaptation with rewardguided optimization, it enhances fine-tuning performance for large models under resource constraints, making LLM adaptation more flexible, interpretable, and accessible.",
    "ContributionsIn this work, I present DRaFT-Q (Dynamic Rank-Aware Fine-Tuning under Quantization), a novel approach for efficient fine-tuning of large language models.",
    "The key contributions of this paper are:1."
  ]
}